'''Charles Francis Brittain''' is an American philosopher currently the Susan Linn Sage Professor at [[Cornell University]]. He specializes in [[ancient philosophy]], specifically [[Hellenistic philosophy]]. His work lies within the Platonic tradition and draws on texts from [[Cicero]], [[Augustine]], and [[Simplicius of Cilicia|Simplicius]]. <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://classics.cornell.edu/charles-francis-brittain |title=Charles Francis Brittain |publisher=cornell.edu |accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-nb99160061/ |title=Brittain, Charles |publisher=worldcat.org |accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref>

