{{Infobox saint | name = Gregory of Tatev | image = Commentary to David's psalms - portrait of Grigor Tatevatsi 1449.jpg | imagesize = | alt = | caption = Grigor Tatevatsi (from a 15th-century Armenian manuscript) | titles = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1346 | birth_place = [[Tmogvi|Tmkaberd]] (now in [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] | home_town = | residence = | death_date = 1409 or 1410 | death_place = | venerated_in = [[Armenian Apostolic Church]] | beatified_date = | beatified_place = | beatified_by = | canonized_date = | canonized_place = | canonized_by = | major_shrine = | feast_day = | attributes = | patronage = | issues = | suppressed_date = | suppressed_by = | influences = | influenced = | tradition = | major_works = }}
'''Gregory of Tatev''', or '''Grigor Tatevatsi''' ({{lang-hy|Գրիգոր Տաթևացի}}) (1346&ndash;1409 or 1410) was an [[Armenia]]n [[Philosophy|philosopher]], [[Theology|theologian]] and a saint in the [[Armenian Apostolic Church]]. He was born in [[Tmogvi|Tmkaberd]] (today in [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]).<ref>{{cite book|last=Karapetian|first=Samvel|title=Javakhk|year=2011|publisher=[[Research on Armenian Architecture]]|location=Yerevan|isbn=978-99941-875-7-7|page=192|url=http://www.raa-am.com/Book_9Eng/amboxg_poqr.pdf|authorlink=Samvel Karapetyan (author)|ref=harv}}</ref>
A monument to Tatevatsi was unveiled on October 16, 2010 in [[Goris]], Armenia.<ref>[http://www.netnewspublisher.com/monument-to-14th-century-philosopher-grigor-tatevatsi-unveiled-in-goris-armenia/ NetNewPublisher]</ref><ref>[http://www.panarmenian.net/eng/society/news/55341/Monument_to_philosopher_Grigor_Tatevatsi_unveiled_in_Goris PanArmenian.net]</ref>
